  "bio": [
    "Seth Boro is a managing partner at software-focused private equity firm Thoma Bravo, which was ranked as world's top buyout investor in a 2019 report.",
    "The firm, with assets of $131 billion, was formed in 2008, when Orlando Bravo and Carl Thoma split from partner Brian Cressey, who was focused on healthcare deals.",
    "Boro holds an MBA from Stanford and heads the firm's cybersecurity and infrastructure software practice.",
    "He joined Thoma Bravo in 2005 after stints at Summit Partners and Credit Suisse, and became a managing partner in 2013.",
    "His family foundation, Room to Breathe, focuses on youth mental health issues in under-resourced communities."
  ],
  "about": [
    "Boro was ranked in Mergers & Acquisitions Magazine's \"Rising Stars\" and San Francisco Magazine's \"40 Under 40.\""
